George's Restaurant is a beautifully updated family-friendly establishment with high quality diner food at reasonable prices. Their chicken souvlaki platter and corned beef sandwiches are delicious. The coleslaw is not my favorite but I can live without that. If they were open and delivered 24/7 I would give them an extra half-star. I am excited to go back and try more things!
The food was on point I went and bought a cheeseburger deluxe and oh my gosh!!!! So happy for the new staff the renovation
Ok but nothing special. 3.5 stars Pros: can bring your own beer, friendly and fast service. Cons: food could be better for the price. New decor is bland and dull. Tip: Buffalo wings suck. Gyro is ok.

Best sit down breakfast food and service in the neighborhood. Recently renovated kitchen and eating area looks superb. I have lived here over 30 years and yearned for a replacement to the original George's diner fare and experience. Over the years management changed and downsized in quality and restaurant size. But they are now back with great family atmosphere and quality ingredients. Highly recommended for a hungry bear or a model looking for a snack.
I love their cheeseburgers! Very delisious and cool atmosphere.

Overpriced. Like way overpriced for what it was. We ordered mozzerella sticks which are $8.25. When I got them, they were literally still frozen in the middle! I got a burger. You could tell the meat was not fresh. How? It had that freezer burned taste. I can't speak for my boyfriend's pasta dish but what we got sure as he knows ain't worth $40. I'm seriously wondering if I'm gonna see this place on Kitchen Nightmares. It looks like one of those once great places that Gordon Ramsey loves to revamp.

★★★★★ I ordered a burger with saute onions and mushrooms It was delicious... not cheap with the mushrooms and onions a good size burger not to thick 🍔 that is always a plus👍👍👍 because you can savor every bite you take. The place is clean, great service, friendly and decent prices.

Wow. I'm so glad I waited until seeing more reviews about George's to see everything so on point.  I'm not very into diner style food but this, this is what all diners should be like.  We walked in and were greeted by a friendly gentleman who managed to seat us right away even though the place was packed. Water and menus were brought right away.  We ordered 3 different style egg dishes and gosh those portions are huge. And so so good. Tasty, hearty and the perfect breakfast delight. The service topped all. Our waitress was friendly and the food came to our tables stat. Free refills on coffee.  The food is very well priced for the portion sizes.  Parking was perfect on this rainy Saturday. We managed to park right out front.  I think George's has now become my favourite weekend spot. It's exactly what this neighborhood needs.

The Italian omlette they serve is great. Loaded with mozzarella cheese, roasted tomatoes and mushrooms. Service is astounding even on weekends. They make very good spinach cooked in olive oil an garlic. the coffee is terrific and they don't charge for a second (or even third) cup like most other restaurants in the neighborhood. This is the NEW reopened Georges.
Love the place
EXCELLENT.....
Really tasty burger!

Steady reliable old school diner. My Dad used to get his lunch here in the 90s when he was working and now I work in FiDi and come here for breakfast.  Solid outdoor seating on Greenwich. Plenty of indoor tables and a separate take out counter. Gets busy at lunch but the staff is efficient and professional.  They do refill your coffee reliably. They do being the check quickly when it is requested but they don't breathe down your neck if you are lingering over coffee chatting with your friends during a not too busy hour.  This is plain and simple a real nice classic New York diner. Nothing fancy, nothing crazy. Dependable and pleasant for breakfast, lunch or dinner.

Last week we went on a Saturday night and the place was clean, well lit and the food was delicious. I had the fried chicken wich was unbelievably good, crispy seasoned batter and moist delicious chicken inside. Loved it!

The older gentleman in the kitchen at nights was doing a horrible job. He gave me bad ricotta cheese In my baked ziti. Also he was puting his finger in his nose all of the time. It was just disappointing For me. Also i found black tomatoes in my sandwich

George's is a family owned restaurant started in 1956. Over the last few months relatives of the original owners and their partners gutted the interior, replaced all the equipment, fixtures and furnishings. The restaurant opened this morning, Monday, December 7th.  I am so thrilled that George's is back! It has been the heart of the neighborhood for many, many years. I hope it will thrive and continue to be a shining beacon.  The food is solid and reasonably priced. Nothing fancy. Just good food and good vibes

I would have given 0 stars if it was possible. Tried to order a delivery and the guy on the phone was very rude, didn't specify how long it will take for the order to get delivered 2 blocks, didn't want to give the amount of the order and told that I'm the one who has to call back to get the amount of the order. The food is sub par, overpriced, and the service is atrocious. Please don't order from this place, you'll regret it.

I moved into the neighborhood about three years ago, and I was glad to see George's, a diner about two blocks from my house. Then I tried the place. First of all, there were roaches on the wall. The manager looked like he hadn't taken a shower or washed his clothes for years. As far as the waitress was concerned, her having to work at her age was simply elder abuse. As for the food: I ordered a London Broil Sandwich. When I bit into it, I had to check my shoe to see if someone hadn't secretively stolen some leather from it and placed it between two slices of bread. I will definitely not go there again, and unless you're into really slumming it, I would suggest that you pass it up.
Unless the older gentleman is working you can expect terrible service. Staff is rude, looks lost most of the time.

This is not the George's Restaurant of yesteryear.  Over the past 15 years, this place has gone from a restaurant with great service and diner-ish food, with an AMAZING cheesecake, to being owned by people who don't have a clue about restaurant management. George's once occupied nearly four storefronts, so it's sad to see it in its current state.
